          "body": "The procedure of verses 14-18 is a masterpiece of narrative tension. Tribe, clan, household, man — four concentric circles, each one closing around the guilty party. The verb for each selection is *lakhad* — the same word used for capturing enemy cities. Judah is taken; the Zerahites are taken; Zabdi's household is taken; Achan is taken. The reader already knows who it is (7:1, 18) — but the narrative slows to maximum deliberateness to make the point: nothing is hidden from God. The lot is not chance; it is providential revelation. Proverbs 16:33 states it plainly: 'The lot is cast into the lap, but its every decision is from the LORD.' The four-stage narrowing also has a pastoral function: it gives the guilty party time to step forward. Between the announcement of the procedure (7:14-15) and its execution (7:16-18), there was a night (7:13). Achan did not come forward. The narrowing was not mercy exhausted — it was mercy extended and refused."
